[b][size=150]Compatibility[/size][/b]
Tested and working on Firefox Stable/Dev. Edition, SeaMonkey and Palemoon.
[b][color=#FF0000]Not compatible with Thunderbird, Nightly nor Windows Vista[/color][/b]

[color=red][size=150][b]Changelog - Updated June 17, 2016[/b][/size]
[list][*] Now there is no need to edit the button to change its settings.
[*] Added compatibility for Palemoon and SeaMonkey.
[*] Added menu item to SeaMonkey to restore all tabs.
[*] Added menu item to clear the list of closed tabs.
[*] Now the button looks and behaves exactly the same ([i]almost[/i]) in the three applications (Firefox, Palemoon and SeaMonkey).[/list][/color]

[size=150][b]Features[/b][/size]
[list][*] Middle click functionality for the menu on SeaMonkey (it restores closed tabs to the the end of the tabs bar, like Firefox/Palemoon by default).
[*] Access keys for the first nine menu item for Firefox/Palemoon (like on SeaMonkey by default).
[*] Both menu items added by this button ([b]Restore All Tabs[/b] and [b]Clear closed Tabs list[/b]) can be localized (from this button options).[/list]
[b]Note:[/b] SeaMonkey seems not to save the favicons for the closed tabs, so the menu of closed tabs will not have images like Firefox/Palemoon does.

[size=150][b]Options[/b][/size]
[list][*] [b]pMenuOnly:[/b] If set to true, the button will be a "menu type" button that will display a menu with the list of recently closed tabs. If set to false, the button will be a "menu-button type" button that when clicked will restore the last closed tab and its dropmarker will display the list of closed tabs.
[*] [b]pShowAccessKeys:[/b] Add access keys to the first nine items of the menu.
[*] [b]pShowRestoreAllTabsAlert:[/b] Show an alert or not when trying to restore all closed tabs ((like on Firefox/Palemoon by default)).
[*] [b]pShowClearClosedTabsListAlert:[/b] Show an alert or not when trying to clear the list of all closed tabs.[/list]

